Broadmind Special Projects Limited has put all machinery in place to organise a special training, talent hunt, exhibitions, and fun-time with a special need for every individual particularly youths, women in Gombe, Northeast of Nigeria as part of an effort to reduce unemployment and social-vices in the country. The upcoming mind-blowing event, according to the Project Coordinator, Arc. Akinfenwa Mobolaji in a statement on Saturday, is slated for July 4th – 10th is tagged, “Build And Groove: Gombe 2022” will create an avenue for training opportunities for individuals, professionals who wish to gain more professional insights and learn entrepreneurship in advanced and learning levels. Akinfenwa disclosed that, the area of specialisation include data analysis, programming for starters, polystyrene ceiling installation, flexi-clay materials installation, photography and other lucrative activities. “Also, talent hunt for individuals contest in different technical and life skills in construction, graphics design, calligraphy, art paintings, hair weaving/beauty makeup and others. “Exhibition opportunity will also be available for brands and individuals to showcase rheir products and services. Entertainment which is the main event that will roundup a week-long program. “Some nation’s top celebrities such as Buzu, Sani Danja, Ali Jita, and much more in the entertainment industry will be performing at the event, while awards for the winners in the competitions, training, empowerment will be presented on July 10, 2022”.